  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n\r\n## Problem \r\nIf you sync device1 and device2, create a community, and receive a membership request, it will appear on device1 only.\r\nAfter relogin, the request appears on device2 as well.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nThe membership request is displayed on both devices without relogin\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nThe membership request is displayed on the primary device only until relogin on the secondary device\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n1. Recover the same account on device1 and device2\r\n2. Sync device1 with device2 (tap the `Sync all devices` button on device1 only)\r\n3. Create a community and post the invite link in some public chat\r\n4. Join the same public chat on device3 and send a membership request to the community \r\n5. Check the Membership requests screen on device2\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: nightly 21/12\r\n- Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n\r\nDevice1 [geth.log](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/files/7756066/geth.log)\r\nDevice2 [geth.log](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/files/7756069/geth.log)\r\n\r\n",
